reviews.text:
The food was absolutely fantastic, excellently made.  It was also quite sizeable and kept my fiancée and I filled the rest of the day; we ate around 11 in the morning.
Our waitress was polite and quick with her service, but she seemed distanced and not very happy.  Maybe there's something I don't know, but it made it hard to have happy communication.
It's a little pricy, about $17-30 a meal, but it was worth it.  If you have a coupon, I recommend going.

I don’t live near this place but have met friends for lunch several times. The steak salad was delicious as well as the mushroom burger. I also really liked their fries. Our server Paige was attentive and helpful. It also has a fun vibe. I definitely recommend it.

Amazing service by Emily and the food is delicious! Thoroughly enjoyed the sweet potato fries and fry sauce and lava cake. Highly recommend! Very cute decor and ambiance, the food came out quickly, great serving sizes, and our server Emily was very sweet. Glad we stopped here when we visited from California!

First timer for me today!   I ordered the Baja and RRG burger! The food was excellent and the service was outstanding! We had Emily as our server and she was so attentive and enthusiastic about her job! She was quick to get our food and drinks too.  It makes a fun experience when your server is so friendly! I will be back for sure and recommend requesting Emily for your server. PS… the caramel sauce with the sweet potato fries… out of this world!

This place was great! The prices weren’t too bad and the portions were very generous! We wanted to try a few different things so we got some steak fries and poutine as well as a chicken sandwich. It was all very tasty! The poutine was incredible and it had fried cheese curds instead of the normal mozzarella ones. I loved it! Definitely would recommend to anyone and will definitely be back!

Pathetic excuse for a taco bell. By far the worst I've been to. The quality here is insanely variable and is usually gonna be poor. The people here are slow to get orders down it's like it's always their first day. They also love to skimp out on sauces and are constantly out of items.

The picture I'm posting shows one of the worst items I have ever gotten here. A Mexican pizza THEY DIDNT EVEN CUT with the cheese slid to one side dripping off the edge. Sadly this is the only one near Rexburg and I strongly recommend going elsewhere.

My wife got a double stack taco and it almost had nothing in terms of the cheese sauce or fiesta strips. Almost no meat and bad quality lettuce. This location regularly skimps out and we only come here because it's close

Never have been so disappointed in a Taco Bell before. Expect this place to skimp on servings. The portions are pathetic. Ordered the Steak and Garlic Nacho Fries, a nearly $7 menu item, and was met shear disappointed.

This was by far one of the dirtiest and most disgusting restaurant I have been to in the last year. Poop on the floor, trash in the kitchen, uncovered employee drinks, and blocked fire exits. I’d say they were just too busy to take care of it, but they were slow enough for employees to be scrolling on their phones. See pictures if you dare.

The portion size pictured does not match what is advertised.

The crunchwrap supreme barely had any ingredients. It was mostly tortilla. The 5 layer burrito was actually more of the size of the cheesy wrap.

I paid $17 in total for my meal. $14 for a whole sandwich and $3 for a starter ice cream. I got half way through my sandwich (which I took to go and was no longer close by) and noticed that my club sandwich (turkey, ham, and roast beef) had one slice of roast beef… it was a good sandwich but that’s not worth the money for me and I don’t plan on going back.

I've only had their frozen yogurt. It is really good. We usually get a chocolate frozen yogurt with cookie dough on top. I've only been there around 8 pm. They seem fairly busy at that time, but I've only had to wait for a little bit to order only once. I can usually pull up, order, get my order, and be back in my car in about 5 minutes (except for 1 time).

This was a quaint little restaurant in Rexburg Idaho. They offer sandwiches, salads, yogurt and shakes. We got sandwiches and chips. Next time we will try the shakes and yogurt. They had grilled or cold sandwiches and plenty of toppings to your design. It was a nice stop for a quick and healthy bite. Definitely will return.

Classic Rexburg spot for ice cream. Sandwiches are okay. DO get the Italian sandwich. DO NOT get the grilled chicken sandwich. As far as the ice creams go they're all pretty good.
I would say you will definitely need at least a whole sandwich. Unless you're not hungry at all I would recommend not getting the half one.
Parking is kind of limited but for whatever reason I've never had problems finding a spot to park.

Paid $32 for two sandwiches and two small bags of chips, waited 25 minutes for the food and halfway through our food we realize there was only a single slice of folded meat on both sandwiches we ordered!

This isn’t the first time we’ve received a sandwich from Millhollow with hardly any meat on it but this is the last! We are done spending our money here! I don’t know how this restaurant gets away with charging $13 for one sandwich with only one slice of meat on it, so ridiculous!

I don’t know if it was just because it was the end of the day, but the pizza I got was horrible, it was so soaked in grease that half of it was inedible, this is probably because there was twice as many sausage pieces than usual. The cheesy bread was fine, but the pizza was not.

We ordered some of their most difficult pizzas and it took a while for them to be ready. However, once we arrived to pick up the pizza, it was obvious why. Over a dozen people were waiting in the lobby for their pizza with more arriving. The fact that it took them 20-25 minutes to make our pizzas turned from questionable to incredible. The pizza was hot and delicious, they even gave us extra Parmesan on the pepperoni. 10/10 would recommend, this place is awesome

I’m not one to give 1 star reviews, but this place has major issues with consistency. Every time I get a cheese pizza from here, which is almost weekly, the center of pizza is paper thin. I end up throwing out almost half a pizza. I will take my business elsewhere. It appears they just care about food cost and not about quality.

The pizza was cold. This Little Cesar's is located in Rexburg Idaho. I don't like this restaurant anymore because they have changed. I used to be able to call in and get to order my pizza making sure they would have some but they've refused me. Using the app doesn't work anymore. Even their prices have gone up. I'm disappointed.

For the price, it’s hard to pass on the pizza. However, the employees are often grumpy and slow. A woman came in after me with a pickup order, which was already behind, and asked about her order. They explained that it was almost ready. When it came out, instead of handing it to her, since she was standing there, they ignored her and put the order in the pickup cabinet. Seemed odd to see that. Examples like that attest to the overall lack of customer service.

This is the best pizza in Eastern Idaho. It's worth the drive from Idaho Falls. Great tasting sauce and the crust came out perfect. The split level dining area is nice and quiet on the upper floor. Salad was solid too.

Holy Pizza! So I’ve learned over the years that some of the best pizza places you’ll ever find are near college campuses. Makes sense. College kids and pizza are almost synonymous.

My family was in Rexburg and decided to pop into Righteous Slice and I’m so glad we did! The staff was super friendly, we got to chat with the owner who was super cool, and the pizza was amazing!

The pizza seems to be a superb blending of Naples-style crust with American-style toppings. The owner is very knowledgeable about the art of pizza dough (yes, it’s an art and that’s not up for debate) and has trained his staff to respect the process.

When the staff recommended the Bee Sting, I was hesitant but decided to trust them. Honey on a pizza? Whelp, I’m glad I gave it a go. It was AWESOME!

If you’re in the Rexburg or Idaho Falls area, Religious Slice is worth every penny. Highly, highly, highly recommend!

The absolute best pizza in all of Idaho! They import all ingridents from Italy! The pizzas are hand made to order and 100% fresh everytime. We ordered just a standard pepperoni pizza to try for the first time and it was so delicious and flavorful! My whole family devoured the entire thing in a short sitting! It was so intensely flavorful and so so so good! I can not say enough good things about their pizza, willing to drive 45 mins everytime I want pizza it is so good! If you haven’t tried their pizza, you are surely missing out. They also have fresh squeezed lemonade! So good! And the prices were very fair for everything being imported and authentic Italian ingredients. This place can not be beat for quality, price, and service! The pizza is even good next day reheated! Please stop in and give this place a try, you won’t regret it. It also has some pretty awesome views with the second floor seating! Enjoy! I know we did!

I have been able to get to know Bill as a professional and as a friend. Every detail is thought about when serving customers here. The ingredients, the employees hired, and the physical atmosphere, everything is deliberate.

This is by far some of the best pizza I have had over my lifetime. You will not be disappointed if you give it a try.

Well... They have 2 types of pizza, New York and Neopolitan. They had some very creative combinations. The gal taking the order was obviously new, but was very personable and helpful. The rest of the staff we spoke to were equally amazing. Good job and kudos to the hiring manager, especially in this day and age!

The dough was good and the pizza was cooked to perfection. However, I ordered onions, (not on there) , and cooked tomatoes, there were very few. They messed up and put uncooked tomatoes on top (probably because they didn't see the cooked ones). I will admit, I really liked the uncooked tomatoes too, so that was a bit of a win.

Couple strange things.
I ordered spinach, but you can't have that on the NY because it burns. Okay, fair enough. I paid the premium for the prosciutto because I love the way the edges get a little crispy when it gets cooked. They just took the prosciutto out of the package and threw it on top after the pizza was cooked. When I asked to have it cooked on, they said it would shrivel up too much.
I don't know if you've ever tried to cut prosciutto with your teeth, but it's a no go. So you just get one big slap on the chin and then you have to shove the whole piece in your mouth... As well as being a bit embarrassing, I just don't like a big mouthful in only one bite. The rest of the slice is a half of tomato and cheese. Not so great, at least for me. So beware of that.

The other thing to be aware of is the soap dispenser in the bathroom. You should check it out for the sheer fun of it.

DON'T EAT THE POPCORN!
Each and every time with come here, the popcorn, or maybe it's the extra butter they spray on it, makes us sick!  Throwing up at one in the morning is no fun!
Seats need work so they don't lay back so far, The floors are super sticky and should probably mop in-between movies.
On a positive note, it's a cheaper theater. We usually do the summer movies deal with our kids cuz the price is perfect. The staff is super awesome and friendly. We also really love the soda selection.
Such a great experience! I watched the chosen today and just before closing Vanessa helped get what I needed. Thank you so much, Vanessa! She was so kind!

It wasn't too bad.  There was a small line that took longer than I had expected it to last, but I think some of the families were the ones taking their time.
The seat felt more comfortable than last time, I did go the last movie theater... 5, I think.
Go on a Tuesday for best price. Parking is slim pickens. Employees were friendly. Theater is older but clean. I don't like having to pick / reserve your seats... I wish seats were FCFS.

My wife and I go to the theater every now and then. The prices of the tickets and the food are fairly reasonable. They also have a rewards program which is pretty neat you can get a lot of points and redeem for snacks or free tickets.

Great place for volleyball, Frisbee, general activities, walking, running, some water activities (though that's currently not operating). Great spot for dates. Not super secluded, but generally a pretty great park.

Porter Park in Rexburg is awesome! It's super spacious, well-kept, and perfect for a picnic or just relaxing. It’s always so peaceful, and there’s plenty to do. Definitely a go-to for a laid-back day outside!

Porter Park is a really well maintained park in Rexburg Idaho. It's big and full of activities with people always doing something. There are restrooms, a basketball court, space to set up volleyball nets, a playground big toy for kids, and a tennis court. There's also a pavilion for concerts. It's a great park. There are aot of trees close together so people can set up hammocks. Also apparently horses hang out here. If you like spikeball, frisbee, volleyball, or slack lining this is the place to go. Across the street they have Jimmy John's, Five Guys, and some other restaurants.

We found this park by accident.  It has amazing trees and green grass.  The kids played on the playground and then the free water park area.  The splash pad has water slides!  The kids played for 3 hours. There is also tennis courts.  Everyone there was super nice.  This is now one of our favorite parks.

Great place for walking dogs, rollerblading, casual longboarding. In the summer the splash pad  is a great place for small kids. There are often musicians playing in the amphitheater and there are many places to eat in walking distance.

I have never been to Freddy’s—ever—and I’ve been missing out! I ordered their spicy hamburger with a Turtle Concrete Mixer, and my husband ordered a bacon cheeseburger with a side of fries and a concrete mixer. The fries are julienne-cut, and their texture is amazing: crisp with some chew, and are perfectly salted. My burger was smashed thin, giving the edges a delicious, delicate crispiness, but it was also very salty, a bit too salty for me. Otherwise good spice and flavor. My absolute favorite was the mixers. I’ve never experienced such smoothness in a frozen dessert, only disrupted by the pecans, which while tasty, I wish I didn’t have. Very creamy and satisfying; and bonus point: they use REAL whipped cream! Will definitely come again!

Originally gave a 3 star review due to the single burger. I have been a few times since, and everything else has been great. So, I still wouldn't order the single burger, but onion rings, fries, and double burger are all really good.

Leaving the original post below:
Never order the single burger... If I realized it had 1/2 the meat of a burger somewhere else at 2x the price, I would have just paid the extra 60 cents for a double. I'm honestly not sure what I paid for because the cheese looks like kraft cheese, the bun tastes like a cheap 39 cent bun, and the meat looked like someone threw some ground beef on the grill for a minute and didn't even bother to flip it over.

I usually only get fries and custard here, which are pretty good. But probably the last time I order a burger. And definitely last time I'll order the single burger.

First time at a Freddy's and I don't know how it will ever be matched. The food was actually so dang good. The hospitality was incredible, the whole staff really deserves a shout out, only got Dylan's and Spencer's name, but, whoever took our order was super nice and helpful as well. Clean restaurant. Delicious food. Top notch hospitality. Truly was a 5/5 experience.

Following my rather discerning and meticulously crafted review, I found myself ensconced in the delightful embrace of communication just shy of three revolutions of the sun, wherein I was generously offered a complimentary voucher to remedy my prior experience, which had left much to be desired. Now, I must take a moment to cast blame upon the whims of the postal service—those nefarious couriers of confusion—rather than upon the goodly establishment known as Freddy's, for it was their intentions that were wholly pure and unblemished. Upon my return visit, I was met with profound apologia and an exuberant eagerness to furnish me with a gastronomic escapade far superior to my previous encounter, which was akin to dining with misfortune itself. In what seemed like the mere blink of an eye—five fleeting minutes, to be precise—my culinary creations arrived at my table, resplendent and seemingly dripping with the promise of ambrosial delight. Each morsel was a symphony of flavors, tantalizing my palate as if they had indeed summoned the culinary spirits of excellence! Thus, I find my faith in the wondrous world of Freddy's magically restored! With immense enthusiasm, I would HIGHLY recommend this establishment to all those who hold dear the pursuits of delectable cuisine and unforgettable experiences!

I just tried Freddy's catering for the first time. I ordered online and did a pickup order. The food was ready when I arrived and conveniently packaged. I received a lot of positive feedback that the food tasted great. Overall, it was a great experience, and I will definitely use Freddy's catering services again.

This is the worst Chickfila ever! My wife and I ordered 2 deluxe chicken sandwiches with no tomato. The only thing they put on the sandwiches was the tomato. So I paid the deluxe price for 2 plain sandwiches because we took off the tomato.
Bruh. They think they are too good for anything like the rewards app or even gift cards. A Chick-Fil-A that doesn't accept Chick-Fil-A. Like what the heck
I wish you could use the app here. Also, so many menu items are just plain missing from the location. Other than that, it’s the same great quality you expect, and the employees are always nice.
The expeditor this afternoon was phenomenal! So friendly, showed genuine interest and care for all the patrons. This kid needs a raise!!!

I ordered just a Dr. Pepper from their kiosk and waited 20 minutes then when I went up to ask about they said I never even bought one..... it was rude and they didn't really care to help figure it out....

I tried the Nashville chicken sandwich. This was so crispy and juicy! Probably the best chicken sandwich I've had. A little Spicier than I expected, so if you love heat, this one's for you! The waffle fries we're also perfect and crispy. The service was great and they were very fast. Can't wait to try more of their menu items!

The flavor was okay, but it didn’t look good. The fries and brisket seemed like they were sitting there for a few hours before we picked the order up. Ribs were really yummy. It was almost $30 for a two person order. Unless I’m craving ribs, I don’t think I’ll come back.

What a great find.
Amazing fresh fries from the original Idaho potato’s.
Very juicy brisket and the tasty smokey tri-tip. First time here and great food experience.
Of course inside a gas station store it’s not the best atmosphere.
They deserve their own place !! Highly recommended. Great personnel.

Went on date night tonight with my husband! We have loved Blisters from back when it was stuck in a gas station and now it has spread its wings and moves to a bigger and wayyyyy better location!

I recommend this to any and all who needs a winter pick-me-up!!!
We got a date night special- Two brisket sandwiches, two fries, and two drinks for $20!

I love you Blisters!!!!!! ❤️

**Update for new location: they put me on hold for 20 minutes so I just drove there before they answered lol. The place wasn't full or anything. The food is good though. I waited around 20 minutes for 2 items. I'll update again next time I come.

**Old: Best BBQ in town. Never had a problem with the food or service. Food is usually ready in 10-15 minutes. If you go a bit late expect them to have ran out of ribs.
I do have to say that I feel they used to give bigger portions a while ago, but even now it's plenty of food.
